<subSubSection id="C33E6517FFEE6653FF39950A545EF871" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9B369CFFEE6652FF39950A536CF94E" blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" box="[151,801,1642,1667]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="B950EA8EFFEE6652FF39950A5164F94F" bold="true" box="[151,297,1642,1667]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including forewing). Male: 
<quantity id="4CDC9B79FFEE6652FD6A950B5350F94E" box="[708,797,1643,1667]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B369CFFEE6652FF6995EE547FF8DF" blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Brownish. Head and thorax marked with dark irregular markings symmetrically placed on crown, anteriorly and medially on pronotum. Gena and lorum light brownish without markings except a pair of small brownish spots bellow eye. Mesonotum with both ends of the suture bent upward and a dark markings posterad of scutellar suture. Forewings smoky brown, with some transverse veins white and without markings.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B369CFFEE6652FF69947E5218F896" blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Anteclypeus distinctly tapered from base to apex, slightly more than twice as long as basal width, apex concave; clypeal suture weakly arcuate.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B369CFFEE6652FF6994065181F827" blockId="8.[151,1437,1642,2027]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">
Male abdomen. 
<number id="3DEC24BBFFEE6652FE24940751D5F8B3" box="[394,408,1895,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="2.0">2</number>
T apodeme with submedial lobes very short and rounded laterally; 
<number id="3DEC24BBFFEE6652FB629407549AF8B3" box="[1228,1239,1895,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="1.0">1</number>
S apodeme with submedial lobes straight, greatly elongated, ca. 4.0 times longer than wide, lateral extension bifurcate, branches subequal in length, dorsal branch slender and lateral branch broad; 
<number id="3DEC24BBFFEE6652FC2C94CF53DCF80B" box="[898,913,1967,1991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="2.0">2</number>
S apodeme with submedial lobes short, slender and strongly curved mesad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B369CFFEF6653FF39951552BCF920" blockId="9.[151,1435,1653,1772]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="B950EA8EFFEF6653FF3995155159F947" bold="true" box="[151,276,1653,1675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
FIGURE 
<number id="3DEC24BBFFEF6653FEAF95155142F947" box="[257,271,1653,1675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C244D1FFFEF6653FEB29516518BF947" box="[284,454,1654,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B950EA8EFFEF6653FEB29516518BF947" box="[284,454,1654,1675]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">Evinus obscurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26357F5FFEF6653FE6395165253F947" box="[461,542,1654,1675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, Male, dorsal view; B, head, dorso-anterior view; C, face; D, male, lateral view; E, male pygofer, lateral view; F–G, connective and aedeagus, lateral and ventral view; H–I, 
<number id="3DEC24BBFFEF6653FBE895F6541EF960" box="[1094,1107,1686,1708]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="2.0">2</number>
nd abdominal tergite, dorsal and anterior view; J–K, male 
<number id="3DEC24BBFFEF6653FE0C95D851E2F902" box="[418,431,1720,1742]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="1.0">1</number>
st sternal apodeme, dorso-anterior and anterior view; L–M, male 
<number id="3DEC24BBFFEF6653FBFB95D8542FF902" box="[1109,1122,1720,1742]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="2.0">2</number>
nd sternal apodeme, dorsal and anterior view; N–O, male pygofer, caudal and ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9B369CFFEF6653FF699474545EF871" blockId="9.[151,1437,1812,2017]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">Male genitalia. Pygofer lateral lobe relatively short, ventral margin strongly concave, posterior margin rounded. Subgenital plate with lateral lobe triangular, not reaching dorsal margin of pygofer lobe. Connective Yshaped, branches longer than stem and weakly divergent. Aedeagus with shaft abruptly narrowed and bent dorsad near midlength and strongly curved anterodorsad near apex in lateral view, lateral margins convex near base and parallel-sided near apex in posterior view, constricted near base in ventral view.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
